2500|$|In all, six {{lines of}} berms have been constructed. [...] The main ("external") line of fortifications extends for about [...] It runs east from Guerguerat {{on the coast}} in the extreme south of Western Sahara near the Mauritanian town of Nouadhibou, closely parallelling the Mauritanian border for about , before turning northwards beyond Techla. It then runs {{generally}} northeastward, leaving <b>Guelta</b> Zemmur, Smara, crossing again Mauritanian territory and reaching Hamza in Moroccan-held territory, before turning east and again closely following the Algerian border as it approaches Morocco. A section extends about [...] into southeastern Morocco.|$|E
