50|$|The {{local economy}} is {{centered}} on agriculture, with production of wheat, dates, figs, grapes, and root crops. Camels, cattle and goats are grazed, and fishing from the <b>gueltas</b> is also significant. There is also some tourism associated mainly with the nearby frescoes.|$|R
50|$|Iherir {{is located}} at an {{elevation}} of 1070 m above sea level. Its valley is an oasis containing <b>gueltas</b> and numerous date palms. The town is notable for the dramatic rocky mountain ranges that rise as much as 300 m on all sides. Prehistoric art dated to 9000 BC {{is found in the}} area. The valley is protected as a nature park, but protection applies only to the frescoes, not to the fauna or flora.|$|R
